# Cleave project context

- Currently in the build out / proof of concept stages. Phase 5 Milkdrop (M5): [scripts/milkdrop_visualizer.py](scripts/milkdrop_visualizer.py) four libprojectM layers at 1280x720, 30 fps, stem PCM; manual M2 sync sign-off still user-run. Phase 5.6 live tuning UI: focus-driven overlay ([cleave/viz_tuning_overlay.py](cleave/viz_tuning_overlay.py), [cleave/viz_tuning_controls.py](cleave/viz_tuning_controls.py)) with **track rows section** (per-stem preset/blend/opacity/beat tree plus collapsible **cleave effects** header and per-effect depth rows; preset dir/file rows use Material Icons folder/file glyphs) and **footer rows section** (Material Icons transport controls, save); overlay icons via bundled [assets/fonts/MaterialIcons-Regular.ttf](assets/fonts/MaterialIcons-Regular.ttf) and [cleave/viz_material_icons.py](cleave/viz_material_icons.py); preview with [scripts/material_icon_probe.py](scripts/material_icon_probe.py). Arrow-key navigation, z-order move mode, layer lock (Ctrl+Enter on track header, red padlock icon, `layers.*.locked` in config), SAVE CONFIG snapshots to [saved-cleave-configs/](saved-cleave-configs/) via [cleave/config_snapshot.py](cleave/config_snapshot.py). See [.cursor/rules/live-tuning-ui.mdc](.cursor/rules/live-tuning-ui.mdc) for layout terms. Phase 6 cleave effects complete: signal-driven compositor modifiers (pulse, flare, flash, hue, grit) in [cleave/effects/](cleave/effects/); config under `layers.*.effects`; plan in [docs/cleave-effect-plan.md](docs/cleave-effect-plan.md). Phase 7 next: usability and packaging. Phase 4 pygame baselines: [scripts/layered_visualizer.py](scripts/layered_visualizer.py), [scripts/pulse_visualizer.py](scripts/pulse_visualizer.py).
- See [docs/cleave-build-plan.md](docs/cleave-build-plan.md) for the build plan.
- See [README.md](README.md) for the project overview.
- Stem layout: `stems/<trackname>/` with four wavs plus `signals.json`. Visualizers: pulse and layered (Phase 4 pygame); milkdrop (Phase 5 libprojectM, stem PCM).
- As the project evolves, update the build plan and README to reflect the current state.
